Step 1 — Connect to EC2 Instance via AWS Console:
    Go to AWS Console → Navigate to EC2
    Click on Instances and select your running instance
    Click the "Connect" button at the top

Step 2 — Connect to Instance Page:
    It will redirect you to the "Connect to Instance" page
    You will see multiple connection options:
    ✅ EC2 Instance Connect(easiest — browser based)
    SSH Client
    Session Manager
    RDP Client
    Stay on the "EC2 Instance Connect" tab
    Click the "Connect" button at the bottom of the page

Step 3 — Result:
    It will redirect you to a browser-based EC2 terminal (command line) 
    where you are already connected to your EC2 instance — no PuTTY or .pem file required!
